            <p>שלון בת ליעזר</p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation" ana="#b1" xml:id="jeru0019.translation" corresp="#jeru0019.transcription">
            <p>Shalon, daughter of Li'azar.</p>
         </div>
      <div type="edition" subtype="transcription_segmented"><p><w xml:id="jeru0019-1" xml:lang="arc">שלון</w> <w xml:id="jeru0019-2" xml:lang="arc">בת</w> <w xml:id="jeru0019-3" xml:lang="arc">ליעזר</w></p>
</div>
</body>
      <back>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>The ossuary has low feet and traces of yellow wash. Height refers to height of chest plus that of lid. Ornamentation, on the chest's front side, consists of two metopes and a broadened triglyph that contains a plant with triangular base and seven branches terminating in lanceolate leaves. Both metopes are surrounded with line and zigzag frames and contain six-petalled rosettes within concentric line circles. שלון is an alternate form or contraction of the name שלומציון, attested in Greek writing in a local inscription and on Jewish tombstones found in Italy. ליעזר is a contraction of אליעזר or אלעזר familiar from the Jerusalem Talmud.</p>
         </div>
